{{info}}**Question:** What visual effects will the following CSS rules introduce when applied on a HTML page?

{{code language="css"}}
body, p, div, span {
  background-color: blue;
  color: white;
  font-family: Georgia;
  font-weight: bold;
}
a, a:hover, a:visited {
  color: blue;
  font-family: sans-serif;
  font-size: 14px;
  text-decoration: none;
}
{{/code}}

Are there possible issues caused by the css rules above?{{/info}}
